{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"alias":"paradoxal-balsamic-bubblefish","description":"## Why\nA local `rebar review-code` run persists NOTHING today (the sidecar emit is gated on `target_ticket`, which the local path never sets), so local reviews cannot converge across iterations. To give local reviews finding memory keyed on the coding-agent session, the local path must resolve a session key and emit a `code_review` artifact.\n\n## What\n- Resolve the local memory key via the centralized `rebar._commands.session_id.resolve_session_id()` (precedence REBAR_SESSION_ID -> CLAUDE_CODE_SESSION_ID -> OPENCODE_SESSION_ID -> SESSION_ID). Validated: this is shared across subagents in one session and unique per parallel session.\n- FALLBACK when it returns None (bare/headless, no SessionStart shim): mint a per-invocation uuid4 (do NOT persist to a shared file). This guarantees isolation and no local->Gerrit bleed; genuine per-session convergence comes from the SessionStart shim wherever a session lifecycle exists. Approved approach (A).\n- Wire the local gate entry (src/rebar/_cli/_llm_commands.py `_review_code` -> code_review/shim.py `review_code` -> gate_dispatch.produce_code_review_verdict) to emit a `code_review` artifact under the typed key `session:<id>`, reusing the existing sidecar.emit path; `relates_to`-link the resolved ticket (from --ticket or the head commit's rebar-ticket trailer) for searchability.\n\n## Scope\n- src/rebar/_cli/_llm_commands.py, src/rebar/llm/code_review/shim.py, src/rebar/llm/workflow/gate_dispatch.py.\n- Depends on the payload shape from the reader/payload story.\n- Out of scope: the Gerrit voter path (already emits; only inherits the payload extension).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] Local `rebar review-code` emits a `code_review` artifact keyed `session:<id>` with the reviewed-file deps map.\n- [ ] Session key = resolve_session_id(); when None, a per-invocation uuid4 is used (no shared-file persistence).\n- [ ] The artifact `relates_to`-links the resolved ticket when one is available; a trailer-less/ticketless review still persists (memory keyed by session), degrading to no cross-run match only when the key differs.\n- [ ] Test: two sequential local reviews under one session id share the key; a different session id does not.","id":"3bff-cdf6-8fca-4c33","parent_id":"374d-9aaf-7d5b-4331","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"story","title":"Persist a code_review artifact for local rebar review-code + session keying (uuid fallback)"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783625843441518001,"uuid":"baa61a91-d6c3-486c-b786-7d789bf7b316"}